content.description: At a high point move up and right across open slab to the corner, climb the corner (great gear) for 50' then straight up the wonderfully textured (moon rock) low angle slab with pro maybe every 25' to an overlap at about 125' then traverse right for about 50' along the base of the overlap to the trees 50. The overlap finish looks challenging and about 40 higher.
content.protection: good gear most of the way up to '3 but if making the traverse a '4 would be helpfull   Double ropes were used

content.description: Climb The Iron Heel past the end of the corner flake and to the first 3' overlap, traverse right  under the overlap ~50' to a tree island (optional belay). Wrestle through the tree island to gain the rock again, staying just left of the vegetation (reaching right for gear occasionally) and heading for trees at the right end of the large overlap. Rappel with double 60m ropes.
very clean slab with moderate routes and good features (moonrock) Located in a great area with a lake and camping
